<subSubSection id="AE1AA0BFE87EDF451967287DB79638BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8B2A08DC7A46E724B1A5B61A8A5F39C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81BED9E2F8927DB364B0589D0D56D053" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="DAE77DAB2C61A551170DBF9866EB4A7E" author="Kifune, T" journalOrPublisher="Tohoku Konchu Kenkyu" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B41" refString="Kifune, T, Maeta, Y, 1965. A tentative list of the Strepsiptera. Part I. The genus Pseudoxenos Sanuders, 1872 (Stylopidae). Tohoku Konchu Kenkyu 2: 1 - 10" title="A tentative list of the Strepsiptera. Part I. The genus Pseudoxenos Sanuders, 1872 (Stylopidae)." volume="2" year="1965">Kifune and Maeta (1965)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a new replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="29E865E36A6BD478C21D7A5A722846E0" authority="Schultze, 1925" authorityName="Schultze" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Macroxenos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macroxenos piercei" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piercei">
<emphasis id="104D12AFFF32E0EDA7CAB9F316296FEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Macroxenos piercei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schultze, 1925, a secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="FAE3D992FACC607A9C279360AE096C5B" authority="Pierce, 1908" authorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Ophthalmochlus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophthalmochlus piercei" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piercei">
<emphasis id="7CE1C1EBBF19EEA87EA5EF40917DBD67" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophthalmochlus piercei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="E11657C0ADA2BADFED565F7F69E5E797" originalValue="Brèthes">Brethes</normalizedToken>
, 1923 (now 
<taxonomicName id="92D3E0D9DD7B1B4519C77C4B7E68DFC5" authority="Pierce, 1908" authorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Brethes" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Eupathocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eupathocera piercei" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piercei">
<emphasis id="43818924A2F7C04A6806D79CC46E0BA5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Eupathocera piercei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="9D53C48D85BD742560E28120CA0FD2A6" originalValue="Brèthes">Brethes</normalizedToken>
, 1923), comb. nov.) when both were placed in the same genus 
<taxonomicName id="C211D8F0E866E88101A3F3FCF7F689D7" authorityName="Saunders" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Pseudoxenos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudoxenos" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CA1FB9A78321379FC837FFE48F8ED80F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudoxenos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="39B5F5F305130D9814A81CDAAFD948C0" authority="Schultze, 1925" authorityName="Schultze" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Macroxenos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macroxenos piercei" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piercei">
<emphasis id="94AD26AB2BE780F9236B5B171D88A58D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Macroxenos piercei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reinstated here as a valid name following the Article 59.4 of 
<bibRefCitation id="6DCD3AE81E043A168B07FDE349E0F08A" author="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B29" refString="ICZN, 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, [XXIX +] 306 pp." title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, [XXIX +] 306 pp." year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
